DataElement.preferredName: Well Differentiated Liposarcoma Primary Diagnosis Month Number
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Numeric value that represents the month of the primary diagnosis of well differentiated liposarcoma.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A locally aggressive mesenchymal neoplasm composed either entirely or partly of an adipocytic proliferation showing at least focal nuclear atypia in both adipocytes and stromal cells. "Atypical lipomatous tumor" and "well-differentiated liposarcoma" are synonyms describing lesions that are morphologically and genetically identical. Amplification of MDM2 and/or CDK4 is almost always present. (WHO 2020)_Occurring first in time or sequence; original; of greatest rank or importance or value._The investigation, analysis and recognition of the presence and nature of disease, condition, or injury from expressed signs and symptoms; also, the scientific determination of any kind; the concise results of such an investigation.
